{"/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_dowe_ver01/data/sn92073229/00332891844/1957121701/1019.xml":{"full_text":"Tuesday, December 17, 1967\nIsraeli Diplomat\nWill Lecture Here\nThe Carolina Forum has an\nnounced that its second speaker\nof the academic year will be\nAbba Cban, Israeli Ambassador\nto the United States, who will\nspeak at 8 p. m. January 8 in\nHill Hall under the auspices of\nthe Forum, a non-partisan stu\ndent organization which brings\nprominent lecturers to the cam\npus.\nA leading scholar of Middle\nSELECT AND REGISTER\nYOUR PATTERN\n(at least 6 weeks before your wedding)\nil\nl I STERLING\n_\njjgfC\nI son do your favorite Sterling pattern\ng&A w well in advance of your\nr\u00abs\\'(wedding day. Your friends\n&2SLW and relatives will appreciate\nflj your (^>ou for\ngift selections will be easier\n(oe\u00bb'E\\) and accurate (no duplica\nthe earlier you make your\nctadt SIRASBQUS6\nat hk i choice and register it the\nWITH A more Sterling you'll receive.\nSINGLE Why wait choose\nI TEASPOON cufsti yourj ,od;,y!\nFROM indud f*d Tom\n*4.25 u ivnr r 4 j,\n\\triy\u00bbs to \u2014-SJff\n*T*AM MU\nWentwoxtli Sloan\nJEWELERS\n167 E. Franklin St. l\u2019hone 9-3331\n(f\\\n1\nsoil\ntfic J\nI l Mil G\nhere ngw just in time for Christmas\nnew KODAK\nCAMERA OUTFITS\nColor-Slide t\u00a3 Kodak\nMiniature S|gnet 40\nRangefinder Camera\n2- 1- y fl s iu\nKODAK JIONIT 40 Df lUXf\nOUTFIT with 6-Shol Kodak\nlotary FlaiHoicUr, othor photo\naid\u00bb, $96.00.\nKODAK JIGNIT 40 COLOR-\nSlIDi OUTFIT with J-i\u00ab*\u00abt\u00bbr\nRath, brilliant Kadak 300\nProjector, preview Mreen,\n131 SO.\nFREE INSPECTION\nOs Yo\u25a0r\nFlash Unit\nand\n1\nBatteries\nDon\u2019t Be Disappointed on\nChristmas Morning\nS*S4.imUa\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014MSA-AA\u2014AJ\u2014. <\u00abl\u00bbii4 11111 l\nEastern affairs, Mr. Eban has\nbeen Israel's representative in\nthe United States since 1950.\nAn active member of the Zion\nist movement, he appeared be\nfore the Political Committee of\nthe United Nations in 1949 to\nplead the case for Israel\u2019s ad-\nI mission to the United Nations.\nMr. Eban was born in South\nAfrica and grew up in England,\nwhere he attended Cambridge\nUniversity and later was a mqm\nber of its faculty as an authority\nlon Hebrew, Arabic, -and Persian\ni literature.\nMOVIES roe\nfjmlltt Comoro, 1/2.7\nn, v 2925\nHe* low price for a\ngenuine Kodak Pony miniature\nOther Kodak color-tlide camerae\nI here, too\nhere, lee\nBlakely Leng Is Married to George Poe\nlift J Njl\nMB \u25a0awl. a I\nwy fl M KiaK\nI j\nK' --f J. Jg\nI Wv%} f\nMR. ANI) MRS. GEORGE WAYNE POE\nMiss Blakely Leng, daughter\nof Mr. and Mrs. E. H. Leng,\nwas married to George Wayne\nI\u2019oe, son of Mr. and M rs George\nPoe, at five o\u2019clock, Friday, De\ncember 6, at the Chapel Hill\nPresbyterian Church.\nThe Kev. Vance Barron and\nthe Itev. Samuel Hubei officiat\ned at the double-ring ceremony.\nMiss May Marshbanks provided\nnuptial music.\nGiven in marriage by her\nfather, the bride wore a white\nbrocade sheath dress with u cowl\nneckline and a backdrape of chif\nfon, white elbow length gloves,\nand a white picture hat. She\ncarried a Bible covered with car\nnations and hybrid cypredium.\nMiss Donna Ballenger was the\nmaid of honor. She wore a red\ntaffeta princess dress with mat\nching jacket and carried a coloni\nal nosegay of white carnations.\nRalph Macklin was best man for\nthe groom.\nNOTICE OF SALE\nUnder and by virtue of the\nauthority of an Order of the\nClerk of Superior Court of Or\nange County entered in the Spe\ncial Proceedings entitled \"Willie\nHargraves, et al vs Beatrice Fid\nwards, et al\u201d, the undersigned\nCommissioner will sell at public\nauction to the highest bidder for\ncash on the premises in the Town\nof Carrboro, N. C\\, on\nWEDNESDAY, JANUARY 8,\nlUSH at 12 o\u2019clock Noon\nthe following described proper\nty:\nFIRST TRACT: All that cert\nain lot or parcel of land situat\ned, lying and being on the South\nwest side of Main Street in the\nTown of Carrboro, N. C., and\nmore particularly described as\nBEGINNING at an iron stake\nin the curb line of said street\nund in C. T. Boyd\u2019s line; run\nning thence with the said street\nSouth 411\u201c Flast 136 feet to a\nstake, a corner of the Jefferson\nproperty; running therice with\nthe Jefferson line South 70\u201c\n15\u2019 West 250 feet to an iron\nstake; running thence North 15\u201c\nWest 126 feet to a rock in a\nstreet in C. T. Boyd\u2019s line;\nrunning thence with the suid\nstreet and Boyd\u2019s line North\n74\u201c 55\u2019 Flast 170.5 feet to the\nj BEGINNING.\nI SECOND TRACT: All that\ncertain lot or parcel of land sit\nuated, lying and being on the\nI Northeast side of Main Street\njin the Town of Carrboro, N. C.,\nand more particularly described\nus B FIG INNING At an iron stake\nin the curb line in the said street\nin C. T. Boyd\u2019s line; running\nthence with the said Boyd\u2019s line\nNorth 75* 16\u2019 Flast 60 sees to\nan iron stake, the Northwest\ncorner of property of St. Paul's\nA. M. K. Church; running thence\nwith the line of the Church\nlot South 26\u201c 30\u2019 East 04 feet\nto an iron stake at the curb;\nrunning thence along the curb\nNorth 40\u201c West 113 feet to the\nBEGINNING.\nTHERE IS RESERVED FROM\nTHE ABOVE DESCRIBED PRO\nPERTY, any part of this pro\nperty now dedicated or used by\nthe Town of Carrboro for side\nwalks.\nThis sale will be reported to\nthe Clerk of the Superior Court\nof Orange County for confirma\ntion, and will remain open for\nten days to receive increased\nbids.\nThis the 6th day of Decem\nber, 1967.\nL. J. Phipps,\nL. J. Phipps\nCOMMISSIONER\nTHE CHAPEL HILL WEEKLY\nThe church was decorated with\na center arrangement of white\nchrysanthemums and snapdrag\nons and an arch of candelabra.\nAfter a wedding trip to Flori\nda, Mr. and Mrs. Poe ure mak\ning their home at 113 Stephens\nStreet in Chapel Hill.\nLocal Man Attends\nRichmond Seminar\nJ. Boyd Flynn of the Univer\nsity\u2019s School of Business Admin\nistration was in Richmond, Va.,\nlast week taking part in a bank\ning seminur at the Federal Re\nserve Bank. He and faculty re\npresentatives of other colleges\nand universities heard talks by\nFederal Reserve officials.\nA native of Washington, N. C.,\nMr. Flynn holds a B. A. degree\nfrom Davidson College and the\nmaster\u2019s degree in business ad\nministration from the Univer\nsity of Pennsylvania\u2019s Wharton\nSchool of Business Administra\ntion. He came to Chapel Hill\nthis fall after having taught at\nOhio State University while do\ning work toward a Ph. D. de\ngree.\nGreat Gifts For the Men\ni\nin your Christinas! I\ndress shirts\nHI/ f i ill J F\u2019our collar styles in fine\nH/ 4 I /j ff broadcloth and oxford, all\n\u25a0/\\f i 111,, J II H size*. Always an excellent\nj /J U gift for the men on your\n.1' .1 ii.h.u. -M. I\nSPORT SHIRTS Cass Link SKTB TIES\n398 350 2\u00b0\u00b0\n%l GLOVES\n2 WA\n(Jive a 1 PrQi\nGIFT CERTIFICATE W V C O/\nin any denomination. VNHMHBBi\n-HENNING KR CO.________________________\nPresbyterians Plan\nLexington Meeting\nThe leaders of the Chapel Hill\nPresbyterian Church will take\npart in the Sixth Quadrennial\nYouth Convention of the Pres\nbyterian Church, U. S., to be\nheld from December 28 to 31\nin Lexington, Ky. They are the\nRev. Harry E. Smith, the church's\nminister to students, who will\nserve on the Convention Plan\nning Committee, and the Rev.\nj Vance Barron, pastor of the\nchurch, and Miss Jane Sutton,\nthe associate to the minister to\nstudents, who will be two of the\none hundred Bible leaders who\nwill teach a concentrated Bible\nstudy.\nMore than 2,000 senior high\nschool and college students from\n16 states will attend the con\nvention on the campus of the\nUniversity of Kentucky. The\nconvention will have four main\nphases: Bible study, major plat\nform addresses by six speakers,\ndaily worship periods, and forty\nseminar groups.\nADMINISTRATRIX NOTICE\nThe undersigned, having quali\nfied as Administratrix of the\nEstate of Duncan J. Ivey, de\nceased, late of Orange County,\nthis is to notify all persons hav\ning claims against said estate\nto present them to tile under\nsigned on or before the 25th\nday of November, 1958, or this\nnotice will be pleaded in bar of\ni their recovery. All persons in\ndebted to said Estate will please\n'make immediate payment to the\nundersigned.\nThis the 25th day of November,\n1967.\nRuth Womble Ivey, Admini\nstratrix of the Estate of\nDuncan J. Ivey\nL. J. Phipps, Attorney\nNOTICE\nOF ADM INSTIGATION\nHaving qualified us executrix\nof the will of Lena Stone Wil\nliams, deceased, late of Orange\nCounty, this is to notify all per\nsons having claims against her\nestute to present them to the\nundersigned within twelve months\nfrom date hereof, otherwise this\nnotice will be pleaded in bar of\ntheir recovery.\nThis December 10, 1957.\nHenry A. Whitfield, Atty.\nI/ena Mae Williams,\nExecutrix of Lena Stone\nWilliams\nNOTICE OF\nADMINISTRATION\nHaving qualified as adminis\ntrators of the estute of Lola\nI.egrand Cheek Riggsbee this is\nto notify all persons having]\nclaims against her estute to pre-1\nsent them to the undersigned\nwithin one year from date hereof\nor this notice will be pleaded in\nbar of their recovery. All per\nsons indebted to said estate are\nreuested to make immediate\nsettlement.\nThis November 5, 1957.\nHenry A. Whitfield, Atty.\nJ. P. Riggsbee and\nWalter B. Riggsbee\nAdministrators of the\nEstate of Lola Le\ngrand Cheek Riggsbee\nADMINISTRATOR'S NOTICE\nThe undesrigned, having qual\nified as Administrator, c.t.a.. of\nthe Estate of Wilhelmina Lloyd,\ndeceased, late of Orange County,\nthis is to notify all persons hav\ning claims against said estate to\npresent them to the undersigned\non or before the 12th day of Nov\nember, 1958, or this notice will\nbe pleaded in bar of their recov\nery. All persons indebted to said\nestate will please make immedi\nate payment to the undersigned.\nThis the 12th day of Novem\nber, 1957.\nThayer Lloyd, Administrator,\nC.T.A. of the Estate of Wil\nhelmina Lloyd.\nL. J. Phipps, Attorney.\nNOTICE\nNORTH CAROLINA\nORANGE COUNTY\nThe undersigned, having quali\nfied as Administrator of the\nEstate of William DeGraffen\nreidt, late of Pittsboro, Chatham\nCounty, this is to notify all per\nsons having claims against said\nestate to present them to the\nundersigned at Pittsboro, North\nCarolina, within one year from\ndate hereof or this notice will be\npleaded in bar of their recovery.\nAll persons indebted to said\nAccent on bfontotW/\n1 Gifting\nOur accessories say, \u201cMerry\nY I w Christmas\" in the nicest pos\nm sible way We\u2019ve everything from\nA. m hankies to handbags, from gloves to\nf) Yk umbrellas.\n0\nA. Slim Jims and regular umbrel\nfjJdj B. Hand rolled silk squares in\n4^5Y, jjjL, prints and solids. 59c up\n118 l\\ C. Earrings, bracelets, necklaces,\ni pins. Match them up in set*.\nsl-00 each\nlxf D. Leather and Faille In a style\n*1 I 1* or color to suit any costume.\n12.95 up\nattach. \\JT E. uy a box of three for spec-\nial person. $5.00 box up\n.-vN.\\J E. Buy a box of tk for a spec\nwhite and colors. $1.95 pr.\nI (j. G. Imported hand embroidered *r\nkAnln Allt i handprint linens to please uy\n*\\AaJ LvM/O taste. 59e up\nVVU/VIQCH/ Phone 5271\nmpany (T INC. 188Frank,ln8t\n\u25a0\u25a0\u25a0\u25a0\u25a0\u25a0\u25a0\u25a0\u25a0\u25a0MT\u2019* 7 OPEN MON. TfIRU PRI. TILL NINE I\nEstate will please make immedi\nate payment to the undersigned,\nat the above address.\nThis Ist day of November,\n1957.\nL. C. Johnson, Pittsboro, N. C.\nTHE WAY TO GOOD FOODj\nOne Mile Out Durham Hwy.\nAnd You\u2019re at...\nY-.\nij*\n\n:j 4 j:\n!j iji Home of the Finest\nNO STEAKS BARBEQUE\nCHICKEN SEAFOOD\nOpen 4 p.m. (II a.m. Sundays) Till 12\nAdministrator, Estate of\nWilliam DeGraffenreidt,\nDeceased.\nBarber Thompson,\nPittsboro, N. C., Attorneys.\nANDREWS\nPage Three","height":"27081","width":"20245"}}
